name: aster-2002-2003-kansas-satellite-image-database-ksid
notes: The Kansas Satellite Image Database (KSID):2002-2003 consists of image data gathered by three sensors. The first image data are terrain-corrected, precision rectified spring, summer, and fall Landsat 5 Thematic Mapper (TM) and Landsat 7 Enhanced Thematic Mapper (ETM+) imagery covering the state of Kansas, tiled by county in GeoTiff format. While some county triplicates date wholly from either 2002 or 2003, some county triplicates were constructed using imagery from both 2002 and 2003. The TM and ETM+ imagery consists of raw data and visual products in UTM NAD83 Projection. The raw dataset consists of the seven (TM)or eight (ETM+) Landsat bands in their original units (DN values). The visual dataset consists of three products: Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) images, false-colorinfrared composites, and resolution-enhanced natural color composites. KSID: 2002-2003 also consists of two sets of 204 NDVI scenes dreiived from the Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (MODIS)in Lambert Azimuthal Equal Area projection. The first set is the raw NDVI with a data range between 2,000-10,000. The second set is a visual product with data rescaled to a range of 0-200. These products are clipped to the Kansas state boundary rather than the county boundaries. Finally, the KSID: 2002-2003 database consists of 61 precision rectified Advanced Spaceborne Thermal Emission and Reflectance (ASTER) 2001 multispectral scenes in GeoTiff format. The raw dataset consists of three bands in their original units. The ASTER database augments the baseline Landsat-7 imagery databse by providing additional up to date high-resolution imagery over Kansas. The ASTER imagery are scene-based and are in UTM NAD83 Projection.
